Outer and Inner If statements can be any type of if statement (Single if, If…else and Multi-branch If)

•	Single if can be used creating condition for 1 possible output
If (condition) {statements}

•	If … else statement If it resolves to true the first code block is executed. when there are only two option/possibilities ( not more not less than 2 condition)

•	Multi- branch If Statement It is used to make decision among several alternatives. when there are three or more option/possibilities. ONLY one block gets executed.

•	Nested-If Statement Nested if statements can be used for creating a pre-condition. It’s used if one condition can beevaluated to several alternatives."

"o	If (condition) {statements}
Else {statements}

o	Boolean ( logical statement) = true / false
If Boolean { sout;}
Else {sout ;}

o	If (condition 1) {statements}
Else if (condition 2) {statements}
Else {statements}

o	If (condition) {
if (condition) {statements}
else {}
}
Else {}

If Statement without Curly Braces    
•	If there is just one statement in the block so we don't have to use {}
•	If we have more one statement, we have to use {} but the best way is including the {}

Ternaries 
Short is version of if statement. If all the data type is same you can use ternaries.
•	If (condition)  : (condition)?
•	Else=    :
•	Else if (condition)=      :(condition)?

o	String name = (condition)?”even”:”odd”;
o	Sout(name);
o	Sout((condition)?”Even”;”odd”);

o	String name = “”; -> Temporary value.
o	String name; -> variable is not initialized here. Before using it you must initialize it.
o	Boolean name = (logical statement || && logical statement);
o	If (Boolean name // true) string name = “…..” 
o	else if (…condition) string name = “…”
o	Sout (string name)

o	String name = (condition)? “string name” 
o	:  () ? “string name” 
o	: “string name”;
o	Sout (name)

o	Double name = 0;     -> temporary value
o	If (condition) {name = formula // will be assign to the temporary value } else if …

o	Int a = 30;
o	String b = “”; // temporary assigned data will be empty
o	If (logical statement) 
o	{b = “…” ;} // permanent statement
o	Else 
o	{ b = “…”;} // permanent statement
o	Sout ( “ b” ;)
 	

